The funeral
service of versatile commentator Dumile Mateza is underway Bryanston Methodist
Church. The nifty
commentator known as “Phesheya Phaya” died of cancer on Tuesday, 1 February. The former
teacher made his name at the SABC in the 1980s was born in Kareedouw, Eastern
Cape. He was
well-known for doing different sporting codes commentary on both radio and TV
in Xhosa, Afrikaans and English. 